Description: Fragment of oval, tapering handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '151'. Name Damainetos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0114.01.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (125)
